# Test the compiler

Build with

```
make DestDir=~/ulmo

source ~/ulmo/rc

~/ulmo/bin/start_pons
~/ulmo/bin/start_cdbd
```



```
cd /tmp
mkdir test0
cd test0
```

Copy your Welcome.od and Welcome.om sources from the ulmo source root.

Insert those in to database:
```
obci Welcome.od
obci Welcome.om
```

Then build:

```
obbuild Welcome
```

In case you want to modify the source, you can't `obci` it again.

The proper workflow for modifying and recompiling an existing module is:
```
obco -D Welcome
```

This will check out source to disk (Definition + Module)

Then edit Welcome.od and check in again.
```
obci Welcome.od
```

Or use
```
obzap Welcome
```

to remove the module from the DB first, then obci again fresh.

